          <li>World of Warcraft holds the record for the most number of concurrent players in an MMORPG!</li>
          <li>Did you know that the original "Super Mario Bros." was developed in just under two years by a small team of only 11 people?</li>
          <li>Pac-Man, one of the most iconic arcade games, was initially supposed to feature a pizza instead of a yellow circle!</li>
          <li>The iconic sound of the Mario jumping was made using a reversed version of the sound of a person stepping on a tile!</li>
          <li>In the 1980s, the game "Tetris" was actually used by the Soviet government to boost productivity in offices!</li>
          <li>The first video game Easter egg appeared in the 1980 game "Adventure" for the Atari 2600, hidden by the game's developer.</li>
          <li>The "Konami Code," a famous cheat code, was first used in the 1986 game "Gradius" for the NES!</li>
          <li>Did you know the "Halo" franchise started off as a real-time strategy game before becoming the iconic FPS it is today?</li>
          <li>"Minecraft," the best-selling game of all time, was initially created by a single developer named Markus "Notch" Persson!</li>
          <li>The first-ever video game console was the Magnavox Odyssey, released in 1972!</li>
          <li>"The Legend of Zelda" was named after Zelda Fitzgerald, the wife of author F. Scott Fitzgerald!</li>
          <li>The character Mario was originally created as "Jumpman" in the 1981 arcade game "Donkey Kong."</li>
          <li>Did you know "Fortnite" was initially a survival game before transitioning into the battle royale genre?</li>
          <li>The first home console to feature a wireless controller was the Nintendo Wii!</li>
          <li>The "Pokémon" franchise was inspired by the childhood experiences of creator Satoshi Tajiri, who loved to collect insects.</li>
          <li>The "Final Fantasy" series was almost canceled after its first game due to poor sales!</li>
          <li>The most expensive video game ever made is "Grand Theft Auto V," with a production budget of around $270 million!</li>
          <li>"Street Fighter II" holds the record for the most arcade cabinets sold of any game in history!</li>
          <li>The most-played game in the world is "League of Legends" with millions of players worldwide!</li>
          <li>The first game to feature a "boss fight" was "Space Invaders" in 1978!</li>
          <li>Did you know that "The Sims" became the best-selling PC game of all time, surpassing "Myst"?</li>
          <li>The very first VR game ever created was "Sensorama," a 1960s invention by Morton Heilig!</li>
          <li>The best-selling video game franchise in the world is "Mario," with over 500 million copies sold!</li>
          <li>In the 1990s, game consoles were banned in China due to concerns over their impact on children's education!</li>
          <li>One of the most famous video game soundtracks, "The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim," was composed by Jeremy Soule!</li>
          <li>The iconic "Pikachu" from Pokémon was inspired by a combination of a rabbit, a mouse, and a squirrel!</li>
          <li>The character "Link" from "The Legend of Zelda" was originally supposed to be called "Spry."</li>
          <li>The longest video game series in terms of years is "The Legend of Zelda," with its first game released in 1986!</li>
          <li>"Donkey Kong" was the first game to feature Mario as a playable character!</li>
          <li>The character "Crash Bandicoot" was designed to rival Sonic and Mario in the 1990s!</li>
          <li>The "Wii Sports" game, bundled with the Wii console, was the first game to be played by more than 40 million people!</li>
          <li>The first video game to feature a "multiplayer" mode was "Spacewar!" created in 1962 by MIT students.</li>
          <li>The original "Tomb Raider" game was created by a small team, and Lara Croft was inspired by a combination of various strong female icons.</li>
          <li>Did you know that the first video game to be released commercially was "Computer Space," in 1971?</li>
          <li>The largest video game collection in the world belongs to Michael Thomasson, with over 11,000 games!</li>
          <li>Did you know that the best-selling fighting game franchise of all time is "Super Smash Bros."?</li>
          <li>In 2009, the first-ever "virtual reality" gaming console was released, the "Oculus Rift"!</li>
          <li>The first "Resident Evil" game almost had a completely different storyline, with no zombies, and a focus on monster enemies instead!</li>
          <li>Did you know that the iconic "Pong" game was the first commercially successful video game?</li>
          <li>The game "Battlefield 2042" features more than 128-player battles, making it one of the largest multiplayer FPS games!</li>
          <li>Did you know the longest-lasting video game character is "Pac-Man," who made his debut in 1980?</li>
          <li>The highest-grossing video game film of all time is "Warcraft," released in 2016, based on the iconic game series!</li>
          <li>Mario’s full name is Mario Mario, and his brother’s name is Luigi Mario, which makes them both Mario brothers!</li>
          <li>Did you know the first "Call of Duty" game was inspired by the real-life events of World War II and sold millions of copies worldwide?</li>
          <li>The first home console to feature "motion controls" was the Nintendo Wii!</li>
          <li>"Dark Souls" was originally going to have a much simpler, easier difficulty setting, but the developers decided to make it more challenging!</li>
        </random>
        Do you want to read more? If you want we can talk about a gaming platforms like PC, XBox, PlayStation or Nintendo.
      </template>
    </category>
    
